00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:32,640
 Now the new code, index(s,t), close parenthesis, char(s), open square bracket, close square bracket, comma, t, open square bracket, close square bracket, semicolon.

25
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:41,200
 I would note that when we are declaring a character array and we don't give the length of the array, that means that we are inside of a function.

26
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:45,600
 The length of the array exists, but it was from the calling code.

27
00:06:45,600 --> 00:07:01,600
 So char(s), open square bracket, close square bracket, t, open square bracket, close square bracket, semicolon, means parameters s and t are strings of some length, and we will use backslash zero to know when that length is done.

